y. In Draco we find 10.7 +/- 0.9 km s{\textasciicircum}-1{\textasciicircum} including all stars and 8.5 +/- 0.7 km s{\textasciicircum}-1{\textasciicircum} excluding the three stars with the most extreme velocities. These dispersions are consistent with the dispersions measured in the other two studies and confirm that Draco and Ursa Minor have the largest mass-to-light ratios of any of the dwarf spheroidals.},
